Renders one table row (`|-`, `!label`, `|value`) for a single property
on a page. Empty values are skipped entirely (no blank row).

This is a Tier B element renderer — it produces markup using Tier A
primitives (`Property/label`, `Property/value`) and is the primary
override point for per-property customization.

Three ways to customize:

1. **Global override** — edit this template. All property rows wiki-wide
   will change.

2. **Per-property override** — create `Template:Category/property-row/<PropName>`
   (e.g. `Template:Category/property-row/Has_email`). This template gets
   `prop=` and `page=` parameters and full responsibility for emitting
   its row. It is invoked via #ifexist dispatch whenever this template
   is called for that property.

3. **Replace the whole row-rendering pathway** — set `Has display template`
   on the category (see docs/user-guide/customizing-display.md).

Parameters:
* prop - The property page reference (namespaced or bare)
* page - The page or subobject fragment to read the value from;
         defaults to {{FULLPAGENAME}}
</noinclude>
